{"sha": "c97014ce88150584689a2ae9a95d8a40115e0423", "node_id": "C_kwDOANBUbNoAKGM5NzAxNGNlODgxNTA1ODQ2ODlhMmFlOWE5NWQ4YTQwMTE1ZTA0MjM", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Piotr Trojanek", "email": "trojanek@adacore.com", "date": "2022-02-09T16:15:27Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Pierre-Marie de Rodat", "email": "derodat@adacore.com", "date": "2022-05-12T12:38:37Z"}, "message": "[Ada] Accept raise expressions as operands of boolean operators\n\nThis patch restores the previous behaviour of a recently rewritten\nroutine Sem_Ch4.Find_Boolean_Types for boolean operators where one of\nthe operands is a raise-expression, e.g.:\n\n  (raise Program_Error or else (X /= Y))\n\nThis change is required for the Entity field of the \"or else\" operator\nto be set. For GNAT it doesn't matter, but GNATprove requires this field\nto be set.\n\nThe affected call sequence starts at Find_Boolean_Types, goes via\nCheck_Right_Argument and Check_Boolean_Pair to Valid_Boolean_Arg, which\nultimately guards a call to Add_One_Interp.\n\ngcc/ada/\n\n\t* sem_type.adb (Valid_Boolean_Arg): Operands of Raise_Type are\n\tvalid boolean arguments.", "tree": {"sha": "9cc707ab4055e6aeddca6949ea370ce16bdd258d", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/9cc707ab4055e6aeddca6949ea370ce16bdd258d"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/c97014ce88150584689a2ae9a95d8a40115e0423", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/c97014ce88150584689a2ae9a95d8a40115e0423", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/c97014ce88150584689a2ae9a95d8a40115e0423", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/c97014ce88150584689a2ae9a95d8a40115e0423/comments", "author": {"login": "ptroja", "id": 161602, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTYwMg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/161602?v=4", "gravatar_id": "",